Operatives of the Nigeria Police in Adamawa State have killed one suspected kidnapper and arrested two others. The Command said in a statement Tuesday that the operatives recovered one double-barrel gun, some handsets, chains, padlocks, and charms from the suspects. The Police, in the statement signed by Police Public Relations Officer Suleiman Nguroje, said, “On the 16/5/2022, the Command disconnected the criminal network at Gola Hill connecting part of Golantabal, Zumo, Gombi, Maiha and Song local government areas. “The operation, which was carried out by the Command operatives attached to Song Division and the Hunters at Gola Hill situated at a remote side of Zumo District in Song local government area, yielded positive result. “The outcome of these successes followed up on a strategy designed by the command to checkmate cases bordering on kidnapping, armed robbery, Cattle rustling, unlawful possession of firearms, amongst others. “The suspected kidnappers, upon sighting our men engaged them in a gun duel. As a result, one of them was neutralized. Others escaped with bullet wounds.” The police said one Sani Abdullahi, 41 years old, and another, Umar Dantella, 27 years old, both residents of Gombi local government area, were arrested unharmed